{
  "video_id": "pGlZi2SwETc",
  "title": "Math is forever (with English subtitles) | Eduardo Sáenz de Cabezón",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Tomás Guarna Reviewer: Sebastian Betti"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 13370.0,
      "end_time": 19119.0,
      "text": "Imagine you're in a bar, or a club,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19120.0,
      "end_time": 22130.0,
      "text": "and you start talking, and after a while, the question comes up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22130.0,
      "end_time": 24000.0,
      "text": "\"So, what do you do for work?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24150.0,
      "end_time": 26950.0,
      "text": "And since you think your job is interesting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26950.0,
      "end_time": 31230.0,
      "text": "you say, \"I'm a mathematician.\" (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31690.0,
      "end_time": 34800.0,
      "text": "And inevitably, during that conversation"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34800.0,
      "end_time": 37750.0,
      "text": "one of these two phrases come up:"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37750.0,
      "end_time": 41195.0,
      "text": "A) \"I was terrible at math, but it wasn't my fault."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41195.0,
      "end_time": 44613.0,
      "text": "It's because the teacher was awful.\" (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44613.0,
      "end_time": 47582.0,
      "text": "Or B) \"But what is math really for?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47582.0,
      "end_time": 48610.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 48610.0,
      "end_time": 50955.0,
      "text": "I'll now address Case B."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50955.0,
      "end_time": 52510.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52510.0,
      "end_time": 57354.0,
      "text": "When someone asks you what math is for, they're not asking you"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 57354.0,
      "end_time": 60203.0,
      "text": "about applications of mathematical science."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 60203.0,
      "end_time": 61554.0,
      "text": "They're asking you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61554.0,
      "end_time": 65485.0,
      "text": "why did I have to study that bullshit I never used in my life again? (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65485.0,
      "end_time": 67924.0,
      "text": "That's what they're actually asking."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 67924.0,
      "end_time": 72124.0,
      "text": "So when mathematicians are asked what math is for,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72124.0,
      "end_time": 74404.0,
      "text": "they tend to fall into two groups:"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74404.0,
      "end_time": 79738.0,
      "text": "54.51 percent of mathematicians will assume an attacking position,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80609.0,
      "end_time": 85559.0,
      "text": "and 44.77 percent of mathematicians will take a defensive position."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 85559.0,
      "end_time": 89680.0,
      "text": "There's a strange 0.8 percent, among which I include myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89680.0,
      "end_time": 91155.0,
      "text": "Who are the ones that attack?"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 91155.0,
      "end_time": 93902.0,
      "text": "The attacking ones are mathematicians who would tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93902.0,
      "end_time": 95849.0,
      "text": "this question makes no sense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 95849.0,
      "end_time": 98597.0,
      "text": "because mathematics have a meaning all their own --"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 98597.0,
      "end_time": 101143.0,
      "text": "a beautiful edifice with its own logic --"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101144.0,
      "end_time": 103110.0,
      "text": "and that there's no point"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 103110.0,
      "end_time": 105558.0,
      "text": "in constantly searching for all possible applications."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 105558.0,
      "end_time": 107847.0,
      "text": "What's the use of poetry? What's the use of love?"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107847.0,
      "end_time": 110907.0,
      "text": "What's the use of life itself?  What kind of question is that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110908.0,
      "end_time": 112529.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 112529.0,
      "end_time": 116295.0,
      "text": "Hardy, for instance, was a model of this type of attack."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 116296.0,
      "end_time": 118242.0,
      "text": "And those who stand in defense tell you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 118242.0,
      "end_time": 123820.0,
      "text": "\"Even if you don't realize it, friend, math is behind everything.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 123820.0,
      "end_time": 124339.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 124340.0,
      "end_time": 126218.0,
      "text": "Those guys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 126218.0,
      "end_time": 130246.0,
      "text": "they always bring up bridges and computers."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 130246.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132841.0,
      "text": "\"If you don't know math, your bridge will collapse.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132841.0,
      "end_time": 134286.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 134286.0,
      "end_time": 137523.0,
      "text": "It's true, computers are all about math."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 137523.0,
      "end_time": 140800.0,
      "text": "And now these guys have also started saying"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 140130.0,
      "end_time": 145500.0,
      "text": "that behind information security and credit cards are prime numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 145710.0,
      "end_time": 149379.0,
      "text": "These are the answers your math teacher would give you if you asked him."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 149379.0,
      "end_time": 151543.0,
      "text": "He's one of the defensive ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 151544.0,
      "end_time": 153384.0,
      "text": "Okay, but who's right then?"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 153384.0,
      "end_time": 155989.0,
      "text": "Those who say that math doesn't need to have a purpose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 155990.0,
      "end_time": 158849.0,
      "text": "or those who say that math is behind everything we do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 158849.0,
      "end_time": 160519.0,
      "text": "Actually, both are right."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 160520.0,
      "end_time": 162183.0,
      "text": "But remember I told you"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 162183.0,
      "end_time": 165726.0,
      "text": "I belong to that strange 0.8 percent claiming something else?"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 165726.0,
      "end_time": 168929.0,
      "text": "So, go ahead, ask me what math is for."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 168929.0,
      "end_time": 171858.0,
      "text": "Audience: What is math for?"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 171858.0,
      "end_time": 176673.0,
      "text": "Eduardo Sáenz de Cabezón: Okay, 76.34 percent of you asked the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 176673.0,
      "end_time": 179600.0,
      "text": "23.41 percent didn't say anything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 179600.0,
      "end_time": 180827.0,
      "text": "and the 0.8 percent --"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 180827.0,
      "end_time": 183675.0,
      "text": "I'm not sure what those guys are doing."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 183675.0,
      "end_time": 187175.0,
      "text": "Well, to my dear 76.31 percent --"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 187175.0,
      "end_time": 191815.0,
      "text": "it's true that math doesn't need to serve a purpose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 191815.0,
      "end_time": 194685.0,
      "text": "it's true that it's a beautiful structure, a logical one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 194685.0,
      "end_time": 197537.0,
      "text": "probably one of the greatest collective efforts"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197537.0,
      "end_time": 199633.0,
      "text": "ever achieved in human history."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 199633.0,
      "end_time": 201732.0,
      "text": "But it's also true that there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 201732.0,
      "end_time": 206331.0,
      "text": "where scientists and technicians are looking for mathematical theories"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 206331.0,
      "end_time": 208641.0,
      "text": "that allow them to advance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 208641.0,
      "end_time": 212438.0,
      "text": "they're within the structure of math, which permeates everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 212438.0,
      "end_time": 215584.0,
      "text": "It's true that we have to go somewhat deeper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 215585.0,
      "end_time": 217308.0,
      "text": "to see what's behind science."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 217308.0,
      "end_time": 220858.0,
      "text": "Science operates on intuition, creativity."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 221348.0,
      "end_time": 224772.0,
      "text": "Math controls intuition and tames creativity."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 225747.0,
      "end_time": 227937.0,
      "text": "Almost everyone who hasn't heard this before"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 227937.0,
      "end_time": 230647.0,
      "text": "is surprised when they hear that if you take"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 230647.0,
      "end_time": 235186.0,
      "text": "a 0.1 millimeter thick sheet of paper, the size we normally use,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 235187.0,
      "end_time": 238505.0,
      "text": "and, if it were big enough, fold it 50 times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 238505.0,
      "end_time": 244204.0,
      "text": "its thickness would extend almost the distance from the Earth to the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 244600.0,
      "end_time": 247201.0,
      "text": "Your intuition tells you it's impossible."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 247201.0,
      "end_time": 249622.0,
      "text": "Do the math and you'll see it's right."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 249622.0,
      "end_time": 252135.0,
      "text": "That's what math is for."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 252135.0,
      "end_time": 255917.0,
      "text": "It's true that science, all types of science, only makes sense"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 255917.0,
      "end_time": 259288.0,
      "text": "because it makes us better understand this beautiful world we live in."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 259288.0,
      "end_time": 260668.0,
      "text": "And in doing that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 260668.0,
      "end_time": 264179.0,
      "text": "it helps us avoid the pitfalls of this painful world we live in."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 264179.0,
      "end_time": 267657.0,
      "text": "There are sciences that help us in this way quite directly."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 267657.0,
      "end_time": 269412.0,
      "text": "Oncological science, for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 269413.0,
      "end_time": 272904.0,
      "text": "And there are others we look at from afar, with envy sometimes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 272904.0,
      "end_time": 275464.0,
      "text": "but knowing that we are what supports them."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 275464.0,
      "end_time": 278213.0,
      "text": "All the basic sciences support them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 278213.0,
      "end_time": 280649.0,
      "text": "including math."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 280649.0,
      "end_time": 284366.0,
      "text": "All that makes science, science is the rigor of math."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 284366.0,
      "end_time": 289241.0,
      "text": "And that rigor factors in because its results are eternal."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 289242.0,
      "end_time": 291757.0,
      "text": "You probably said or were told at some point"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 291757.0,
      "end_time": 294708.0,
      "text": "that diamonds are forever, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 296178.0,
      "end_time": 298392.0,
      "text": "That depends on your definition of forever!"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 298392.0,
      "end_time": 300883.0,
      "text": "A theorem -- that really is forever."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 300883.0,
      "end_time": 302133.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 302134.0,
      "end_time": 305486.0,
      "text": "The Pythagorean theorem is still true"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 305486.0,
      "end_time": 308601.0,
      "text": "even though Pythagoras is dead, I assure you it's true. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 308601.0,
      "end_time": 309946.0,
      "text": "Even if the world collapsed"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 309946.0,
      "end_time": 312391.0,
      "text": "the Pythagorean theorem would still be true."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 312391.0,
      "end_time": 316452.0,
      "text": "Wherever any two triangle sides and a good hypotenuse get together"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 316452.0,
      "end_time": 317673.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 317673.0,
      "end_time": 320534.0,
      "text": "the Pythagorean theorem goes all out. It works like crazy."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 320534.0,
      "end_time": 323355.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 327535.0,
      "end_time": 331407.0,
      "text": "Well, we mathematicians devote ourselves to come up with theorems."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 331407.0,
      "end_time": 333143.0,
      "text": "Eternal truths."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 333143.0,
      "end_time": 335909.0,
      "text": "But it isn't always easy to know the difference between"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 335909.0,
      "end_time": 338815.0,
      "text": "an eternal truth, or theorem, and a mere conjecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 338815.0,
      "end_time": 341829.0,
      "text": "You need proof."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 341829.0,
      "end_time": 343596.0,
      "text": "For example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 343596.0,
      "end_time": 348423.0,
      "text": "let's say I have a big, enormous, infinite field."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 348423.0,
      "end_time": 352132.0,
      "text": "I want to cover it with equal pieces, without leaving any gaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 352132.0,
      "end_time": 354256.0,
      "text": "I could use squares, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 354256.0,
      "end_time": 358222.0,
      "text": "I could use triangles. Not circles, those leave little gaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 358777.0,
      "end_time": 361134.0,
      "text": "Which is the best shape to use?"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 361134.0,
      "end_time": 365687.0,
      "text": "One that covers the same surface, but has a smaller border."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 365687.0,
      "end_time": 370396.0,
      "text": "In the year 300, Pappus of Alexandria said the best is to use hexagons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 370396.0,
      "end_time": 372243.0,
      "text": "just like bees do."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 372243.0,
      "end_time": 373990.0,
      "text": "But he didn't prove it."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 373990.0,
      "end_time": 376688.0,
      "text": "The guy said, \"Hexagons, great! Let's go with hexagons!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 376688.0,
      "end_time": 379656.0,
      "text": "He didn't prove it, it remained a conjecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 379656.0,
      "end_time": 381334.0,
      "text": "\"Hexagons!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 381334.0,
      "end_time": 384964.0,
      "text": "And the world, as you know, split into Pappists and anti-Pappists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 384964.0,
      "end_time": 390253.0,
      "text": "until 1700 years later"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 390253.0,
      "end_time": 395707.0,
      "text": "when in 1999, Thomas Hales proved"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 395707.0,
      "end_time": 400641.0,
      "text": "that Pappus and the bees were right -- the best shape to use was the hexagon."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 400641.0,
      "end_time": 403123.0,
      "text": "And that became a theorem, the honeycomb theorem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 403123.0,
      "end_time": 405183.0,
      "text": "that will be true forever and ever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 405183.0,
      "end_time": 408224.0,
      "text": "for longer than any diamond you may have. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 408229.0,
      "end_time": 411320.0,
      "text": "But what happens if we go to three dimensions?"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 411330.0,
      "end_time": 414944.0,
      "text": "If I want to fill the space with equal pieces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 415464.0,
      "end_time": 416805.0,
      "text": "without leaving any gaps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 416805.0,
      "end_time": 418638.0,
      "text": "I can use cubes, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 418638.0,
      "end_time": 421994.0,
      "text": "Not spheres, those leave little gaps. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 421994.0,
      "end_time": 424957.0,
      "text": "What is the best shape to use?"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 424957.0,
      "end_time": 429170.0,
      "text": "Lord Kelvin, of the famous Kelvin degrees and all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 429607.0,
      "end_time": 435121.0,
      "text": "said that the best was to use a truncated octahedron"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 436791.0,
      "end_time": 439507.0,
      "text": "which, as you all know --"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 439507.0,
      "end_time": 441350.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) --"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 441350.0,
      "end_time": 442814.0,
      "text": "is this thing here!"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 442814.0,
      "end_time": 445753.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 447778.0,
      "end_time": 449225.0,
      "text": "Come on."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 450250.0,
      "end_time": 452861.0,
      "text": "Who doesn't have a truncated octahedron at home? (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 452862.0,
      "end_time": 454890.0,
      "text": "Even a plastic one."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 454890.0,
      "end_time": 456846.0,
      "text": "\"Honey, get the truncated octahedron, we're having guests.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 456846.0,
      "end_time": 458240.0,
      "text": "Everybody has one! (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 458240.0,
      "end_time": 460614.0,
      "text": "But Kelvin didn't prove it."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 460614.0,
      "end_time": 464655.0,
      "text": "It remained a conjecture -- Kelvin's conjecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 464655.0,
      "end_time": 470176.0,
      "text": "The world, as you know, then split into Kelvinists and anti-Kelvinists"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 470177.0,
      "end_time": 471599.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 471599.0,
      "end_time": 475496.0,
      "text": "until a hundred or so years later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 478203.0,
      "end_time": 482720.0,
      "text": "someone found a better structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 482917.0,
      "end_time": 488250.0,
      "text": "Weaire and Phelan found this little thing over here --"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 488260.0,
      "end_time": 489665.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) --"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 489665.0,
      "end_time": 493209.0,
      "text": "this structure to which they gave the very clever name"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 493209.0,
      "end_time": 495375.0,
      "text": "\"the Weaire-€“Phelan structure.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 495375.0,
      "end_time": 497911.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 497911.0,
      "end_time": 500568.0,
      "text": "It looks like a strange object, but it isn't so strange,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 500568.0,
      "end_time": 502239.0,
      "text": "it also exists in nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 502239.0,
      "end_time": 504844.0,
      "text": "It's very interesting that this structure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 504844.0,
      "end_time": 507370.0,
      "text": "because of its geometric properties,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 507370.0,
      "end_time": 512228.0,
      "text": "was used to build the Aquatics Center for the Beijing Olympic Games."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 512969.00000000006,
      "end_time": 515714.00000000006,
      "text": "There, Michael Phelps won eight gold medals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 515714.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518875.00000000006,
      "text": "and became the best swimmer of all time."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 518875.0,
      "end_time": 522616.0,
      "text": "Well, until someone better comes along, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 522616.0,
      "end_time": 525150.0,
      "text": "As may happen with the Weaire-€“Phelan structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 525150.0,
      "end_time": 527633.0,
      "text": "It's the best until something better shows up."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 527633.0,
      "end_time": 532225.0,
      "text": "But be careful, because this one really stands a chance"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 532225.0,
      "end_time": 537205.0,
      "text": "that in a hundred or so years, or even if it's in 1700 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 537205.0,
      "end_time": 542603.0,
      "text": "that someone proves it's the best possible shape for the job."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 542978.0,
      "end_time": 547348.0,
      "text": "It will then become a theorem, a truth, forever and ever."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 547348.0,
      "end_time": 550301.0,
      "text": "For longer than any diamond."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 550837.0,
      "end_time": 554567.0,
      "text": "So, if you want to tell someone"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 555777.0,
      "end_time": 558823.0,
      "text": "that you will love them forever"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 558823.0,
      "end_time": 560890.0,
      "text": "you can give them a diamond."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 560890.0,
      "end_time": 564420.0,
      "text": "But if you want to tell them that you'll love them forever and ever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 564421.0,
      "end_time": 566172.0,
      "text": "give them a theorem!"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 566172.0,
      "end_time": 567263.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 567263.0,
      "end_time": 569853.0,
      "text": "But hang on a minute!"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 570783.0,
      "end_time": 572183.0,
      "text": "You'll have to prove it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 572183.0,
      "end_time": 574466.0,
      "text": "so your love doesn't remain"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 574466.0,
      "end_time": 576299.0,
      "text": "a conjecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 576299.0,
      "end_time": 579543.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}